RIP P-22 
8/7/2020
The more we learn about him, the more you realize he probably lived a lonely life. 
Apparently, he crossed the 405 freeway headed towards the Hollywood hills about a decade ago, which isolated him from ever finding a mate. 
He was a beautiful, majestic mountain lion, that became an icon/egend.  I remember seeing him about 10 years ago when I was at Griffith Park Observatory on the trails walking with Hunter, Spencer, and Ella. He was up on the hillside, just observing all the people and dogs walking by. 
I then witnessed him walking past my house quite a few times on my security cameras,.
It was usually in the very late evening/early mornings. 
He will always live on in our hearts.
Hopefully we can learn from him, on how we can better serve wildlife creatures like him in the future. 
Let’s learn from our past mistakes to help better our/their future.
#RIPP22 #TeamWEN

Chaz Dean, renowned hairstylist, founder of WEN Hair & Body Care and animal activist, has been tapped as the global Ambassador for the 8th Hollywood Beauty Awards set for Thursday, March 9th, 2023. Chaz is the proud dog dad to Bella and Riley. ♥️🐶🐕

Over the past 30 years, Chaz has built an empire. Starting out as a photographer, he went onto master the art of makeup and hairstyling. A businessman, brand builder and visionary, Chaz went into product creation with the birth of WEN. His trailblazing invention of the first-ever 5-in-1 no-lather Cleansing Conditioner put him on the map. Eventually becoming the number one beauty brand on QVC in 2015, WEN now spans over 700 products and has sold over 50 million Cleansing Conditioners, making WEN one of the largest beauty brands on QVC, while also earning over 50 Customer Choice Beauty Awards. 💆‍♀️

Opening Chaz Dean Studio at 6444 Fountain Avenue in Hollywood, California, the salon has now expanded to three impressive bungalows dedicated to holistic hairstyling. Growing coast-to-coast, Chaz Dean Studio is now open in New York City at 59 Greenwich Ave in the heart of the West Village. 🔥🧘‍♀️👏

It was 22 years ago today that I lost my mom to her battle with Cancer. 
She fought a tough fight from January 1996 through February 5th 2001.
Going through Chemo, Radiation and a Bone Marrow Transplant.
It was tough seeing her health and will to continue to fight decline through those years.  She remained strong until the day her Oncologist told her she most likely had months left to live.
We saw her fighting spirit crumble when she heard those words.
I don’t believe any Doctor or Specialist should ever play God and set time limits on our lives.
I saw the direct effect it had on my mom.
Everyday, I  miss her with all my heart but I know that she watches over me, guides me and protects me. 
When she was first diagnosed with Cancer, she asked me if I would be her Guardian Angel, 
I told her I would as long as she promised to be mine.
Therefore, I know she watches over me through all my battles, struggles,successes and achievements in my life and for that I am grateful.
If I can’t have her here on earth with me, I am blessed to have her watching over me.
Mom, Thank you for all your Unconditional Love you have showered me with.
I know you are always with me.
Sending you absolute love, gratitude and respect.
RIP
Joan Astrid Dean

December 18th, 2019 

I was lucky enough to see the incredibly talented @nickcordero1 at the Premiere of @rockofageshollywood @bourbonroomhollywood 
After the show, I had the honor of meeting Nick, he was so cool, chill and real.
For our first photo he smiled with that beautiful smile he had.
For the second photo he realized I had “serious face” and said “OK let’s do this”.
For the few moments we chatted he left me with a great sense of exactly who he was.
For those of you that know anything about the entertainment industry that doesn’t always happen.
My heart goes out to his family, friends, cast mates, loved ones and anyone that was fortunate enough to meet him.
I know that this is a tough time for all of you but always remember the spiritual being that Nick was.
Use the strength he exuded to help carry you through these troubling times.
Sending absolute light, love and healing blessings to @amandakloots and Elvis.
